Balance¶

The EuroSAT dataset contains 27,000 images over 10 classes. The dataset is fairly balanced, as evident below.

In [ ]:
total_images = 0

# Path to unsplit dataset
path = pathlib.Path('../datasets/eurosat-full/eurosat')

# print the number of files in each sub-directory at path
for subdir in path.iterdir():
  n_images = len(list(subdir.iterdir()))
  total_images += n_images
  print(f'{n_images} - {subdir.name}')

print(f'\nTotal Images in Dataset: {total_images}')

Split¶

The dataset has been split in the following ratio:

80%   Train
10%   Validation
10%   Test

The split was conducted using a custom script: scripts/split_dataset.py which is called by the scripts/init_datasets.sh script. To change the split percentages, update the init_datasets.sh script.

Data Augmentation Demo¶

In [ ]:
# Data Augmentation doesn't work on the M1 Mac GPU
with tf.device('/cpu:0'):
  # Create a data augmentation workflow with flipping, rotation, and zoom
  data_augmentation = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.RandomFlip(),
    tf.keras.layers.RandomRotation(0.1),
    tf.keras.layers.RandomZoom(0.2),
  ])

# Take a single image, and apply data augmentation 9 times over it.
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
for images, _ in train.take(1):
  for i in range(9):
    with tf.device('/cpu:0'):
      augmented_images = data_augmentation(images)
      ax = plt.subplot(3, 3, i + 1)
      plt.imshow(augmented_images[0].numpy().astype("uint8"))
      plt.axis("off")
